{
  "article_id": "Roberts1886",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "THE "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara valley",
        "entity_key": "re_sbvalley",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "has an average width of from two to four miles, and is forty-five miles long. It extends from "
      },
      {
        "text": "Gaviota Pass",
        "entity_key": "re_gaviotapass",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", a narrow passage across the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Ynez range",
        "entity_key": "re_santaynezmts",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rincon Hill",
        "entity_key": "re_princon",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and is divided into three distinct districts. That of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Carpenteria",
        "entity_key": "ci_car",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "lies between "
      },
      {
        "text": "Rincon",
        "entity_key": "re_princon",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ortega Hill",
        "entity_key": "re_ortegahill",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and next to it is "
      },
      {
        "text": "El Montecito",
        "entity_key": "ci_montecito",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which borders the bay and stretches back to the foothills. The third division, the longest of all, is the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara valley",
        "entity_key": "re_sbvalley",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "proper. In it are "
      },
      {
        "text": "the town",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the "
      },
      {
        "text": "village of Goleta",
        "entity_key": "ci_goleta",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and the large fruit and nut ranches nestled at the base of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the range",
        "entity_key": "re_santaynezmts",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "[...]"
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The islands",
        "entity_key": "i_northernchi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "are named "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Rosa",
        "entity_key": "i_sr",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Cruz",
        "entity_key": "i_scruz",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ana Capa",
        "entity_key": "i_an",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They are private property, and are used for sheep-ranges. The ground contains many curious Indian implements, and on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Miguel",
        "entity_key": "i_sm",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "the Spanish explorer "
      },
      {
        "text": "Cabrillo",
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "was buried. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The islands",
        "entity_key": "i_northernchi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "are of various shape and size, one being more than twenty miles long and covered with hills that have an elevation of two thousand feet above sea level. All are the home of myriads of birds, and along their beaches are vast quantities of abalone shells, which are gathered, shipped to "
      },
      {
        "text": "France",
        "entity_key": "co_france",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and made into buttons."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "On "
      },
      {
        "text": "the smallest island [sic]",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "was enacted the tragedy of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the \"Lost Woman of San Nicholas,\"",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "which at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is a familiar tale. The story begins with the removal of "
      },
      {
        "text": "a number of Indians",
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", in 1836. Just as they were embarking, "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the women",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "discovered that "
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "had been left behind. Returning for it, she was abandoned by "
      },
      {
        "text": "her companions",
        "entity_keys": [
          "bhagroup",
          "1835crew",
          "chu",
          "isp",
          "iwi",
          "jsjo",
          "jdy",
          "lbu",
          "natam_hawaiian",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who were obliged by a coming storm to set sail for "
      },
      {
        "text": "the mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". It was intended to return so soon as the weather permitted, but years passed away, and "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "in time was forgotten and left to her fate."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Twenty years later, a hunter named ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", of ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", visited ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for otters. While there, he determined to look for ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". After careful search he found three huts made of whale-ribs and brush, and from where they stood extended an open plain, in the centre of which ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "saw ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the object of his journey",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The woman's dress was made of skins and feathers, and her hair hung in tangled masses from her bare head. ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "When discovered, she was cutting blubber from a seal which she had killed, but on seeing ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her visitor",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "she received him with every manifestation of delight, and readily accompanied him to ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "his boat",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Signs were made [for] her to enter it, and on her doing so, "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "sailed across the bay, and brought "
      },
      {
        "text": "his charge",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Her arrival there created great excitement, and hundreds called at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever's house",
        "entity_key": "nideverhouse",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "to see her. Although she could not have been more than fifty years old, she was gray-haired and emaciated. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Her expression was one of blank ignorance, and her skin was dry and wrinkled. Her language, strange as it may seem, considering the comparatively short time she had been lost, was unintelligible to all. Those who considered themselves masters of every Indian tongue, could not understand a word that she said.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Owing to this fact, the story of her hermitage was never known. What became of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the child",
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "she returned from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to find on that fatal day in 1836, is a matter of pure conjecture. How long it lived and where it was buried were facts that could not be discovered. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "appeared to have lost all human instincts, and to every question asked made no answer that could be understood.",
        "tropes": [
          14
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "In three months after her rescue she died, and was buried by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Mission fathers",
        "entity_keys": [
          "jru",
          "aji",
          "sanchez",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "George Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the hero of the rescue, was a well-known character. "
      },
      {
        "text": "His widow",
        "entity_key": "sni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "still lives at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and the stories of her husband's good qualities and bravery are innumerable. In all accounts he is pictured as a second Leatherstocking, — brave and honest, and familiar with Nature and Indians, the sea and its islands. In an essay on \"Courage,\" "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ralph Waldo Emerson",
        "entity_key": "reme",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "quotes a ballad regarding pure courage, of which "
      },
      {
        "text": "Nidever",
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "is the subject."
      }
    ]
  ]
}